00:14:23.058 --> 00:14:25.350 align:middle line:10%
>>PINCHBECK: What I seek to
offer in "How Soon is Now?"

00:14:25.350 --> 00:14:31.440 align:middle line:84%
is a blueprint for how this
transformation could happen.

00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:35.070 align:middle line:84%
How social systems
are constructed

00:14:35.070 --> 00:14:40.420 align:middle line:84%
has a lot to do with what
type of media is available.

00:14:40.420 --> 00:14:43.270 align:middle line:84%
The internet is now a new type
of media and a new phenomenon

00:14:43.270 --> 00:14:44.740 align:middle line:90%
to reorganize our society.

00:14:44.740 --> 00:14:50.080 align:middle line:90%


00:14:50.080 --> 00:14:53.630 align:middle line:84%
Democratic decision making
could be continuous.

00:14:53.630 --> 00:14:57.010 align:middle line:84%
We could all be part of some
social infrastructure, where

00:14:57.010 --> 00:15:00.600 align:middle line:84%
we make decisions
together all the time,

00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:04.520 align:middle line:84%
it's possible that capitalism is
actually a transitional system.

00:15:04.520 --> 00:15:07.520 align:middle line:84%
Capitalism has brought
the world together

00:15:07.520 --> 00:15:09.080 align:middle line:90%
into one global market.

00:15:09.080 --> 00:15:11.930 align:middle line:84%
It's unified humanity
in a certain sense.

00:15:11.930 --> 00:15:14.480 align:middle line:84%
Everyone can communicate with
each other instantaneously.

00:15:14.480 --> 00:15:19.250 align:middle line:84%
But capitalism is inherently
unstable and also unsustainable

00:15:19.250 --> 00:15:21.680 align:middle line:84%
because it constantly
forces more growth and more

00:15:21.680 --> 00:15:24.720 align:middle line:90%
development.

00:15:24.720 --> 00:15:27.540 align:middle line:84%
Now we've reached the limit
on the finite resources

00:15:27.540 --> 00:15:28.590 align:middle line:90%
of the planet.

00:15:28.590 --> 00:15:30.880 align:middle line:84%
We can't develop
like that anymore.

00:15:30.880 --> 00:15:34.267 align:middle line:84%
So we need to think about a new
model of what development is

00:15:34.267 --> 00:15:35.850 align:middle line:84%
and that form of
development would not

00:15:35.850 --> 00:15:41.030 align:middle line:84%
be more buildings, bigger
skyscrapers, more mining.

00:15:41.030 --> 00:15:43.920 align:middle line:84%
It would be creating a
society that really worked

00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:46.110 align:middle line:84%
for the individual
and provided them

00:15:46.110 --> 00:15:49.400 align:middle line:84%
with a much deeper
level of satisfaction,

00:15:49.400 --> 00:15:54.651 align:middle line:84%
cultural pursuits, maybe
explorations of eroticism even.

00:15:54.651 --> 00:15:57.300 align:middle line:90%


00:15:57.300 --> 00:15:59.540 align:middle line:84%
And I think the things that
truly make people happy

00:15:59.540 --> 00:16:03.890 align:middle line:84%
are love, community, and the
ability to give their gifts

00:16:03.890 --> 00:16:06.355 align:middle line:84%
and feel that they have purpose
and meaning in their lives.

00:16:06.355 --> 00:16:09.310 align:middle line:90%


00:16:09.310 --> 00:16:12.000 align:middle line:84%
There's nature, and then
there's human constructs.

00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:14.520 align:middle line:10%
And those human
constructs, we actually

00:16:14.520 --> 00:16:20.190 align:middle line:10%
have the ability to
redesign, rewrite, revise.

00:16:20.190 --> 00:16:23.550 align:middle line:84%
We just forget that
we have that power.

00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:25.170 align:middle line:84%
One of the most
crucial things is

00:16:25.170 --> 00:16:29.330 align:middle line:84%
going to be kind of
reinventing community, creating

00:16:29.330 --> 00:16:31.910 align:middle line:84%
local communities
or joining community

00:16:31.910 --> 00:16:35.420 align:middle line:84%
groups as a way of breaking
through the separation

00:16:35.420 --> 00:16:39.285 align:middle line:84%
and the alienation that our
capitalist culture has created.

