00:18:35.680 --> 00:18:37.520 align:middle line:84%
It's like we're
actually on a spaceship.

00:18:37.520 --> 00:18:38.320 align:middle line:90%
We've woken up.

00:18:38.320 --> 00:18:39.737 align:middle line:84%
We're the crew of
this spaceship.

00:18:39.737 --> 00:18:41.320 align:middle line:84%
Everything we need
is provided for us,

00:18:41.320 --> 00:18:43.690 align:middle line:84%
except we don't have
an instruction manual.

00:18:43.690 --> 00:18:46.930 align:middle line:84%
So that's what we're
trying to figure out.

00:18:46.930 --> 00:18:48.430 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, if we can't
make it work here,

00:18:48.430 --> 00:18:49.730 align:middle line:84%
we're not going to make
it work anywhere else.

00:18:49.730 --> 00:18:51.310 align:middle line:84%
I think space is just a
fantasy at this point.

00:18:51.310 --> 00:18:53.143 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: When I think
of Buckminster Fuller,

00:18:53.143 --> 00:18:55.630 align:middle line:10%
I think of the geodesic
dome that he created.

00:18:55.630 --> 00:18:58.450 align:middle line:10%
But he was much more elaborate
than just that, wasn't he?

00:18:58.450 --> 00:18:59.290 align:middle line:10%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah.

00:18:59.290 --> 00:19:02.080 align:middle line:10%
He basically looked at
how nature builds things.

00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:04.570 align:middle line:84%
And he and he realized
that nature basically

00:19:04.570 --> 00:19:06.220 align:middle line:90%
never uses right angles.

00:19:06.220 --> 00:19:10.270 align:middle line:84%
And so humans are always seeking
to kind of like dominate,

00:19:10.270 --> 00:19:13.570 align:middle line:84%
control nature, put on these
right angles and so on.

00:19:13.570 --> 00:19:15.940 align:middle line:84%
And so he wanted to create
a whole system of design

00:19:15.940 --> 00:19:17.680 align:middle line:84%
that was more in accord
with nature's principles.

00:19:17.680 --> 00:19:19.360 align:middle line:84%
That's the geodesic dome,
and a lot of his other work

00:19:19.360 --> 00:19:20.380 align:middle line:90%
came out of that.

00:19:20.380 --> 00:19:22.310 align:middle line:84%
And there's a whole
legacy of his work.

00:19:22.310 --> 00:19:24.018 align:middle line:84%
There's the Buckminster
Fuller Institute.

00:19:24.018 --> 00:19:26.110 align:middle line:84%
There's thousands of
ecological designers

00:19:26.110 --> 00:19:28.630 align:middle line:84%
around the world who are
creating new ideas based

00:19:28.630 --> 00:19:29.770 align:middle line:90%
on his principles.

00:19:29.770 --> 00:19:31.228 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: What would
you do, Daniel,

00:19:31.228 --> 00:19:33.010 align:middle line:10%
to start making
this change where

00:19:33.010 --> 00:19:37.037 align:middle line:10%
you would feel comfortable
that something's working here?

00:19:37.037 --> 00:19:38.620 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: You
know, the easiest way

00:19:38.620 --> 00:19:41.590 align:middle line:84%
would be for a major social
network like Facebook or Google

00:19:41.590 --> 00:19:44.230 align:middle line:84%
to recognize that this is
the situation that we're

00:19:44.230 --> 00:19:47.082 align:middle line:84%
in because Facebook can reach
2 billion people in a minute.

00:19:47.082 --> 00:19:48.040 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And instantly.

00:19:48.040 --> 00:19:50.498 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: You know, they
could simply on their home page

00:19:50.498 --> 00:19:52.510 align:middle line:84%
say, dear human
family, we recognize

00:19:52.510 --> 00:19:55.245 align:middle line:84%
that we've entered an
ecological emergency together,

00:19:55.245 --> 00:19:57.370 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to have to
make significant changes

00:19:57.370 --> 00:19:58.578 align:middle line:90%
in the way we live our lives.

00:19:58.578 --> 00:20:01.780 align:middle line:84%
This is going to be including
growing food locally, learning

00:20:01.780 --> 00:20:05.380 align:middle line:84%
bioremediation, learning
permaculture, not doing

00:20:05.380 --> 00:20:07.750 align:middle line:84%
things that are destructive
for the environment,

00:20:07.750 --> 00:20:10.330 align:middle line:84%
redesigning our
manufacturing systems,

00:20:10.330 --> 00:20:13.600 align:middle line:84%
training people to
install renewable energy.

00:20:13.600 --> 00:20:15.790 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to put
all the tools for all

00:20:15.790 --> 00:20:17.862 align:middle line:90%
of that available online.

00:20:17.862 --> 00:20:19.570 align:middle line:84%
Everyone will access
this, and we'll also

00:20:19.570 --> 00:20:23.650 align:middle line:84%
create a decision-making
system using the internet

00:20:23.650 --> 00:20:26.117 align:middle line:84%
that everybody can help
make local decisions,

00:20:26.117 --> 00:20:28.450 align:middle line:84%
regional decisions, and even
planetary decisions better.

00:20:28.450 --> 00:20:31.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So you would use
new technology, social media,

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:33.270 align:middle line:84%
as a platform to help
get this word out?

00:20:33.270 --> 00:20:34.070 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Yes.

00:20:34.070 --> 00:20:38.380 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think that's our
best option because in a sense,

00:20:38.380 --> 00:20:41.800 align:middle line:84%
the internet points towards
the capacity for us to--

00:20:41.800 --> 00:20:43.750 align:middle line:84%
a tool like Facebook
is so incredible.

00:20:43.750 --> 00:20:46.070 align:middle line:84%
It points towards how
we can all be connected.

00:20:46.070 --> 00:20:47.800 align:middle line:90%
We can all find each other now.

00:20:47.800 --> 00:20:50.620 align:middle line:84%
But it restricts our
capacity to use it

00:20:50.620 --> 00:20:53.980 align:middle line:84%
for regenerative social purposes
unfortunately because they're

00:20:53.980 --> 00:20:56.878 align:middle line:84%
trapped in a limited
profit-making model.

00:20:56.878 --> 00:20:59.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You have looked at
blockchain, where of course

00:20:59.170 --> 00:21:00.940 align:middle line:90%
Bitcoin comes from.

00:21:00.940 --> 00:21:02.860 align:middle line:84%
You think that has
some effect on what

00:21:02.860 --> 00:21:04.925 align:middle line:90%
we can do in the future?

00:21:04.925 --> 00:21:07.810 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK:
Blockchain is complex.

00:21:07.810 --> 00:21:10.510 align:middle line:84%
You know, Bitcoin
has pros and cons.

00:21:10.510 --> 00:21:11.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right, it's scary.

00:21:11.800 --> 00:21:12.280 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: What's that?

00:21:12.280 --> 00:21:13.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's scary
as an investment.

00:21:13.410 --> 00:21:15.040 align:middle line:84%
You don't know what's
going to happen.

00:21:15.040 --> 00:21:17.470 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah,
it's kind of--

00:21:17.470 --> 00:21:21.870 align:middle line:84%
the whole thing is very
interesting, very speculative.

00:21:21.870 --> 00:21:23.620 align:middle line:84%
Some of it will become
just infrastructure

00:21:23.620 --> 00:21:28.240 align:middle line:84%
because it's a way
for supply chains

00:21:28.240 --> 00:21:30.670 align:middle line:84%
to track all their
dealings and so on.

00:21:30.670 --> 00:21:32.290 align:middle line:84%
Or for philanthropy,
it's interesting.

00:21:32.290 --> 00:21:35.560 align:middle line:84%
There's a tool called Giveth.io,
where if you put money in,

00:21:35.560 --> 00:21:38.230 align:middle line:84%
you can track it all the
way down to like, oh, look,

00:21:38.230 --> 00:21:42.160 align:middle line:84%
I bought this pencil for this
African refugee or something.

00:21:42.160 --> 00:21:45.790 align:middle line:84%
So I think there's some really
interesting uses for it.

00:21:45.790 --> 00:21:48.630 align:middle line:84%
And it's good that some
of the hype has dissolved.

00:21:48.630 --> 00:21:50.130 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: What's
fascinating about it

00:21:50.130 --> 00:21:54.960 align:middle line:10%
is it's been created not by
institutions, but by people,

00:21:54.960 --> 00:21:56.970 align:middle line:10%
and people are
driving it right now.

00:21:56.970 --> 00:21:58.320 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: That's true.

00:21:58.320 --> 00:22:01.260 align:middle line:84%
And also, you know, for
democratic decision making,

00:22:01.260 --> 00:22:04.500 align:middle line:84%
there's one group, a great one,
called Democracy Not Earth.

00:22:04.500 --> 00:22:06.600 align:middle line:84%
And the idea is to
really create tools

00:22:06.600 --> 00:22:09.420 align:middle line:84%
that would allow people to
make ongoing decisions together

00:22:09.420 --> 00:22:10.500 align:middle line:90%
in a new way.

00:22:10.500 --> 00:22:13.600 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Tell me about
the Tamera in Portugal.

00:22:13.600 --> 00:22:15.480 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah,
so Tamera in Portugal

00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:19.730 align:middle line:84%
is a community that I've visited
a few times that basically it's

00:22:19.730 --> 00:22:21.480 align:middle line:90%
started by German radicals.

00:22:21.480 --> 00:22:25.730 align:middle line:10%
They were trying to figure out
why the great utopian movements

00:22:25.730 --> 00:22:27.690 align:middle line:10%
of the '60s didn't succeed--

00:22:27.690 --> 00:22:31.130 align:middle line:10%
like the green movement and
so on and the left and so on--

00:22:31.130 --> 00:22:33.630 align:middle line:10%
and so they began to realize
that underlying everything were

00:22:33.630 --> 00:22:36.690 align:middle line:10%
core issues of
love and sexuality

00:22:36.690 --> 00:22:40.680 align:middle line:10%
that led to communities to
collapse, the jealousies

00:22:40.680 --> 00:22:41.600 align:middle line:10%
to envies.

00:22:41.600 --> 00:22:45.408 align:middle line:84%
So they call themselves
a Peace Research Center.

00:22:45.408 --> 00:22:46.950 align:middle line:84%
And that's really
what they're about.

00:22:46.950 --> 00:22:49.440 align:middle line:84%
But they say that we're never
going to have peace on Earth

00:22:49.440 --> 00:22:53.220 align:middle line:84%
until we have peace between
the genders and peace and love.

00:22:53.220 --> 00:22:55.140 align:middle line:84%
And for them, that
involves developing

00:22:55.140 --> 00:22:59.400 align:middle line:84%
a whole new social model for
how relationships are organized.

00:22:59.400 --> 00:23:01.150 align:middle line:84%
That includes, like,
most people there are

00:23:01.150 --> 00:23:03.940 align:middle line:90%
in multi-partner relationships.

00:23:03.940 --> 00:23:07.020 align:middle line:84%
Everything that people
do in the private realm

00:23:07.020 --> 00:23:09.420 align:middle line:84%
is actually expressed in the
public sphere and community

00:23:09.420 --> 00:23:11.040 align:middle line:90%
forums, community gatherings.

00:23:11.040 --> 00:23:12.325 align:middle line:90%
It's a very interesting--

00:23:12.325 --> 00:23:13.950 align:middle line:84%
it's like you definitely
feel that it's

00:23:13.950 --> 00:23:15.992 align:middle line:84%
a different world when
you go there, that they've

00:23:15.992 --> 00:23:18.600 align:middle line:90%
created their own new culture.

00:23:18.600 --> 00:23:21.600 align:middle line:84%
And they do peace marches
in Guatemala, peace work

00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:23.670 align:middle line:84%
in Israel and
Palestine and so on.

00:23:23.670 --> 00:23:25.750 align:middle line:84%
But, yeah, I'm
fascinated by them.

00:23:25.750 --> 00:23:26.970 align:middle line:90%
And I'm fascinated by it.

00:23:26.970 --> 00:23:30.450 align:middle line:84%
As I said, it's like I
feel that it's not just

00:23:30.450 --> 00:23:31.940 align:middle line:90%
reforming the current system.

00:23:31.940 --> 00:23:35.380 align:middle line:84%
There's a deeper level system
change that needs to happen,

00:23:35.380 --> 00:23:36.960 align:middle line:84%
and so we need
templates for that,

00:23:36.960 --> 00:23:42.300 align:middle line:84%
both on how organizations
can work collaboratively

00:23:42.300 --> 00:23:47.580 align:middle line:84%
and how communities maybe can
deal with sexuality and love

00:23:47.580 --> 00:23:49.950 align:middle line:84%
in different ways
because obviously we're

00:23:49.950 --> 00:23:52.482 align:middle line:84%
seeing a lot of chaos
around that right now.

00:23:52.482 --> 00:23:54.690 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: As you mentioned,
during the 60s, of course,

00:23:54.690 --> 00:23:57.000 align:middle line:84%
was love and peace
and everything else.

00:23:57.000 --> 00:23:59.543 align:middle line:90%
That fizzled, didn't it?

00:23:59.543 --> 00:24:00.960 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Well,
love and peace,

00:24:00.960 --> 00:24:04.020 align:middle line:84%
it turns out, require
an infrastructure.

00:24:04.020 --> 00:24:07.060 align:middle line:84%
You need a structure that
allows that to succeed.

00:24:07.060 --> 00:24:08.820 align:middle line:84%
You can't just
impose love and peace

00:24:08.820 --> 00:24:12.570 align:middle line:84%
on a military
domination-based empire

00:24:12.570 --> 00:24:15.900 align:middle line:84%
that's based on extraction
and exploitation of resources.

00:24:15.900 --> 00:24:16.950 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't work.

00:24:16.950 --> 00:24:17.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No.

00:24:17.750 --> 00:24:20.880 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we saw what
happened at Tiananmen Square

00:24:20.880 --> 00:24:22.260 align:middle line:90%
with love and peace.

00:24:22.260 --> 00:24:25.590 align:middle line:90%
It just doesn't work sometimes.

00:24:25.590 --> 00:24:28.350 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: My hope would be
that if you could demonstrate

00:24:28.350 --> 00:24:34.350 align:middle line:84%
models for the future that
really made people happier,

00:24:34.350 --> 00:24:36.480 align:middle line:84%
then you could get
everybody onboard.

00:24:36.480 --> 00:24:38.190 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Tell me about
your book, "2012,

00:24:38.190 --> 00:24:40.470 align:middle line:10%
The Return of Quetzalcoatl."

00:24:40.470 --> 00:24:42.330 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: So
that book was really

00:24:42.330 --> 00:24:47.595 align:middle line:84%
an effort to understand
the indigenous cultures

00:24:47.595 --> 00:24:49.470 align:middle line:84%
all around the world
who see this time as one

00:24:49.470 --> 00:24:52.080 align:middle line:90%
of intense transformation.

00:24:52.080 --> 00:24:54.250 align:middle line:84%
And I was looking at
the Mayan calendar,

00:24:54.250 --> 00:24:58.590 align:middle line:84%
which the Long Count of the
Tzolkin, a 5,100-year cycle,

00:24:58.590 --> 00:25:00.240 align:middle line:90%
ended in 2012.

00:25:00.240 --> 00:25:01.647 align:middle line:90%
We're in the next cycle.

00:25:01.647 --> 00:25:02.730 align:middle line:90%
I was looking at the Hopi.

00:25:02.730 --> 00:25:04.260 align:middle line:90%
I visited them in Arizona.

00:25:04.260 --> 00:25:06.780 align:middle line:84%
I was looking at
other phenomenon that

00:25:06.780 --> 00:25:09.870 align:middle line:84%
seemed to relate, like the crop
circles in England, which often

00:25:09.870 --> 00:25:14.460 align:middle line:84%
had information related
to the Mayan calendar

00:25:14.460 --> 00:25:16.500 align:middle line:90%
and so on embedded in them.

00:25:16.500 --> 00:25:22.020 align:middle line:84%
And, yeah, I do think that
we're in the process of going

00:25:22.020 --> 00:25:25.677 align:middle line:84%
through this intense
transformation as a species.

00:25:25.677 --> 00:25:27.510 align:middle line:84%
And all these different
factors are at play.

00:25:27.510 --> 00:25:32.370 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the development
of esoteric knowledge

00:25:32.370 --> 00:25:36.363 align:middle line:84%
and how everyone now does yoga,
knows about Kabbalah and Sufism

00:25:36.363 --> 00:25:38.280 align:middle line:84%
and so on, and that's
moving around the world.

00:25:38.280 --> 00:25:42.960 align:middle line:84%
The rapid accelerated evolution
of technologies that we now

00:25:42.960 --> 00:25:44.340 align:middle line:90%
can communicate with everybody.

00:25:44.340 --> 00:25:49.590 align:middle line:84%
And we can potentially scale
up renewable energy systems

00:25:49.590 --> 00:25:53.310 align:middle line:84%
or whatever we need to do
to help save the planet--

00:25:53.310 --> 00:25:56.070 align:middle line:84%
distributed manufacturing,
automation so that we can

00:25:56.070 --> 00:25:58.255 align:middle line:90%
liberate people from drudgery.

00:25:58.255 --> 00:25:59.130 align:middle line:90%
That's the sad thing.

00:25:59.130 --> 00:26:01.860 align:middle line:84%
It's like if we were to
make this systemic change

00:26:01.860 --> 00:26:03.930 align:middle line:84%
and create this new
operating system now,

00:26:03.930 --> 00:26:05.760 align:middle line:84%
we could actually look
forward to a future

00:26:05.760 --> 00:26:09.150 align:middle line:84%
that really liberates
humanity from a lot of misery,

00:26:09.150 --> 00:26:12.060 align:middle line:84%
where people are really free
to cultivate themselves,

00:26:12.060 --> 00:26:14.100 align:middle line:84%
to explore their
unique individuality,

00:26:14.100 --> 00:26:15.720 align:middle line:90%
express themselves.

00:26:15.720 --> 00:26:18.943 align:middle line:84%
It's just we're in this
bifurcation moment right now.

00:26:18.943 --> 00:26:20.610 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, yeah, so
"2012" looked at it

00:26:20.610 --> 00:26:22.590 align:middle line:84%
at more of a
metaphysical level--

00:26:22.590 --> 00:26:26.850 align:middle line:84%
like, what does this shift mean
in terms of psychic realities,

00:26:26.850 --> 00:26:29.033 align:middle line:90%
consciousness, philosophy?

00:26:29.033 --> 00:26:31.200 align:middle line:84%
And "How Soon is Now?" is
more on a pragmatic level.

00:26:31.200 --> 00:26:34.950 align:middle line:84%
How would we bring about this
change on a systems level?

00:26:34.950 --> 00:26:37.500 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Daniel, ironically,
we're in the Gaia studios.

00:26:37.500 --> 00:26:39.840 align:middle line:10%
And Gaia, of course,
meaning that this planet is

00:26:39.840 --> 00:26:43.090 align:middle line:10%
a living organism-- it's alive.

00:26:43.090 --> 00:26:45.900 align:middle line:10%
Do you think that's true,
that this planet truly

00:26:45.900 --> 00:26:47.938 align:middle line:10%
is alive like we are right now?

00:26:47.938 --> 00:26:50.480 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Well, I think it's
alive but maybe in a slightly

00:26:50.480 --> 00:26:52.737 align:middle line:90%
different way than we are.

00:26:52.737 --> 00:26:54.320 align:middle line:84%
You know, there may
be a lot of things

00:26:54.320 --> 00:26:58.340 align:middle line:84%
that have forms of
consciousness in ways

00:26:58.340 --> 00:26:59.900 align:middle line:84%
that we don't quite
understand yet.

00:26:59.900 --> 00:27:02.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the ancients all
thought that the sun--

00:27:02.630 --> 00:27:04.520 align:middle line:84%
they worship the sun
because they saw the sun

00:27:04.520 --> 00:27:08.555 align:middle line:90%
as an immense, sentient being.

00:27:08.555 --> 00:27:09.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They may be right.

00:27:09.680 --> 00:27:12.263 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Well, I think they
might be right yeah, actually.

00:27:12.263 --> 00:27:14.660 align:middle line:84%
Because if you think
about how the solar rays

00:27:14.660 --> 00:27:17.320 align:middle line:84%
and the solar cycles
and how that influences

00:27:17.320 --> 00:27:19.130 align:middle line:84%
the development, I
mean, maybe the sun

00:27:19.130 --> 00:27:20.588 align:middle line:84%
and the Earth and
the other planets

00:27:20.588 --> 00:27:23.040 align:middle line:84%
are in this very
complex interplay,

00:27:23.040 --> 00:27:26.810 align:middle line:84%
and there is a level of
awareness or intelligence

00:27:26.810 --> 00:27:29.400 align:middle line:84%
beyond what we can
understand that's operative.

00:27:29.400 --> 00:27:34.660 align:middle line:84%
That's also-- ayahuasca, which
is the subject of my new book,

00:27:34.660 --> 00:27:36.770 align:middle line:84%
"When Plants Dream,"
that's also--

00:27:36.770 --> 00:27:37.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I love that
title, by the way.

00:27:37.430 --> 00:27:38.110 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Thank you so much.

00:27:38.110 --> 00:27:39.830 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, that's also
very much a message

00:27:39.830 --> 00:27:43.760 align:middle line:84%
that one gets from
drinking ayahuasca,

00:27:43.760 --> 00:27:45.640 align:middle line:84%
that the planet
is alive, that it

00:27:45.640 --> 00:27:47.390 align:middle line:84%
has an evolutionary
trajectory, that we're

00:27:47.390 --> 00:27:49.630 align:middle line:84%
part of this
evolutionary trajectory,

00:27:49.630 --> 00:27:52.340 align:middle line:84%
and that the whole thing
is very sacred in a way.

00:27:52.340 --> 00:27:54.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Graham Hancock, one
of our dear friends, of course,

00:27:54.920 --> 00:28:00.190 align:middle line:84%
talked about your
book way back in 2010.

00:28:00.190 --> 00:28:04.540 align:middle line:10%
>>GRAHAM HANCOCK: Is it possible
to summarize in relatively few

00:28:04.540 --> 00:28:08.350 align:middle line:10%
words what the essential
thesis of your book "2012"

00:28:08.350 --> 00:28:12.840 align:middle line:10%
is and also the subtitle, "The
Return of Quetzalcoatl?" "

00:28:12.840 --> 00:28:15.430 align:middle line:10%
Why that subtitle?

00:28:15.430 --> 00:28:19.360 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah, well,
I'll start with the subtitle.

00:28:19.360 --> 00:28:25.670 align:middle line:10%
Quetzalcoatl is a Aztec
name for a creator deity

00:28:25.670 --> 00:28:28.185 align:middle line:10%
who's known in the Mayan
language as Kukulkan.

00:28:28.185 --> 00:28:30.310 align:middle line:10%
And it's the feathered
serpent, the plumed serpent.

00:28:30.310 --> 00:28:32.680 align:middle line:10%
So it's the meeting of
the bird and the snake,

00:28:32.680 --> 00:28:35.950 align:middle line:10%
which also could be seen
as the meeting of heaven

00:28:35.950 --> 00:28:38.830 align:middle line:10%
and earth, air and
matter, spirit and matter.

00:28:38.830 --> 00:28:41.200 align:middle line:10%
But also what I
argue in the book

00:28:41.200 --> 00:28:43.630 align:middle line:10%
as a theory is it
could also symbolize

00:28:43.630 --> 00:28:49.210 align:middle line:10%
the integration of previously
seemingly opposed opposites--

00:28:49.210 --> 00:28:52.480 align:middle line:10%
in this case, the
Western materialist

00:28:52.480 --> 00:28:55.720 align:middle line:10%
scientific knowledge
system, which

00:28:55.720 --> 00:28:58.030 align:middle line:10%
would be kind of the Earth,
the material-based one,

00:28:58.030 --> 00:29:00.820 align:middle line:10%
with more of this intuitive,
Shamanic or Eastern

00:29:00.820 --> 00:29:04.220 align:middle line:10%
mystical way of knowing reality.

00:29:04.220 --> 00:29:06.580 align:middle line:10%
And I think that as these
two forms of knowing

00:29:06.580 --> 00:29:08.840 align:middle line:10%
are melding and coming together.

00:29:08.840 --> 00:29:12.333 align:middle line:10%
It's leading towards this
next form of consciousness.

00:29:12.333 --> 00:29:14.500 align:middle line:10%
So that was one element,
and the other element was--

00:29:14.500 --> 00:29:15.520 align:middle line:10%
>>HANCOCK: That's the return--

00:29:15.520 --> 00:29:16.470 align:middle line:10%
>>PINCHBECK: The
return of Quetzalcoatl.

00:29:16.470 --> 00:29:17.170 align:middle line:10%
>>HANCOCK: --that's
what's symbolizing that?

00:29:17.170 --> 00:29:18.280 align:middle line:10%
>>PINCHBECK: Symbolizing, yeah.

00:29:18.280 --> 00:29:20.863 align:middle line:10%
And then the other element for
me personally was an experience

00:29:20.863 --> 00:29:24.100 align:middle line:10%
that I'd had in Brazil, on
the Amazon, where I received

00:29:24.100 --> 00:29:27.088 align:middle line:10%
this transmission of prophecy.

00:29:27.088 --> 00:29:28.630 align:middle line:10%
There was a voice
speaking in my head

00:29:28.630 --> 00:29:31.030 align:middle line:10%
that proclaimed that
it was Quetzalcoatl,

00:29:31.030 --> 00:29:33.820 align:middle line:10%
that this was the apocalypse,
that I had this mission

00:29:33.820 --> 00:29:35.460 align:middle line:10%
to get out these
ideas and information

00:29:35.460 --> 00:29:37.390 align:middle line:10%
and stuff like that.

00:29:37.390 --> 00:29:40.990 align:middle line:10%
So it had resonance for me
both symbolically and then more

00:29:40.990 --> 00:29:42.760 align:middle line:10%
of this personal experience.

00:29:42.760 --> 00:29:45.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How many people
get what we just saw,

00:29:45.040 --> 00:29:46.960 align:middle line:84%
you and Graham
Hancock talking about?

00:29:46.960 --> 00:29:49.810 align:middle line:84%
How many people really
understand what's going on?

00:29:49.810 --> 00:29:51.205 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: I have no clue.

00:29:51.205 --> 00:29:52.080 align:middle line:90%
I don't know if I do.

00:29:52.080 --> 00:29:52.880 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:29:52.880 --> 00:29:53.920 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's honest.

00:29:53.920 --> 00:29:55.652 align:middle line:90%
You better.

00:29:55.652 --> 00:29:56.860 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: I go in and out.

00:29:56.860 --> 00:29:58.690 align:middle line:84%
I mean, sometimes I
toggle back, you know,

00:29:58.690 --> 00:30:02.950 align:middle line:84%
because I had all these
incredible visionary

00:30:02.950 --> 00:30:05.703 align:middle line:84%
experiences and
synchronicities, and everything

00:30:05.703 --> 00:30:07.870 align:middle line:84%
seemed to be building to
some type of amazing thing,

00:30:07.870 --> 00:30:09.880 align:middle line:84%
and then that sort
of melts away.

00:30:09.880 --> 00:30:12.820 align:middle line:84%
Then I'm back in my
small New York apartment,

00:30:12.820 --> 00:30:16.840 align:middle line:84%
trying to figure
out what's next.

00:30:16.840 --> 00:30:19.240 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: For a guy who's
so earthy and concerned

00:30:19.240 --> 00:30:22.210 align:middle line:10%
about the planet, what
are you doing in New York?

00:30:22.210 --> 00:30:23.060 align:middle line:90%
There's no grass.

00:30:23.060 --> 00:30:24.250 align:middle line:90%
It's all pavement.

00:30:24.250 --> 00:30:27.410 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Well, I mean,
I'm indigenous to New York.

00:30:27.410 --> 00:30:28.210 align:middle line:90%
I grew up there.

00:30:28.210 --> 00:30:29.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I mean,
I love New York.

00:30:29.180 --> 00:30:30.910 align:middle line:84%
But I would think
I would see you

00:30:30.910 --> 00:30:32.842 align:middle line:84%
in Montana or
Oregon or something.

00:30:32.842 --> 00:30:34.050 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: I'm not really--

00:30:34.050 --> 00:30:37.540 align:middle line:84%
I'm an urban bohemian and
an intellectual or whatever.

00:30:37.540 --> 00:30:40.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm not really a
nature person, per se.

00:30:40.150 --> 00:30:41.007 align:middle line:90%
I love cities.

00:30:41.007 --> 00:30:43.090 align:middle line:84%
I love the density of them,
and I grew up in them.

00:30:43.090 --> 00:30:44.010 align:middle line:90%
My dad was an artist.

00:30:44.010 --> 00:30:46.000 align:middle line:84%
My mother was a
writer and an artist.

00:30:46.000 --> 00:30:51.280 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, it's my
natural habitat.

00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:54.840 align:middle line:84%
I'm not really
some nature person.

00:30:54.840 --> 00:30:57.970 align:middle line:84%
The reason I'm talking about all
this stuff around the ecology

00:30:57.970 --> 00:30:59.530 align:middle line:90%
is that I have a daughter.

00:30:59.530 --> 00:31:01.210 align:middle line:90%
You have a granddaughter.

00:31:01.210 --> 00:31:05.470 align:middle line:84%
Whatever is going
on in our brains,

00:31:05.470 --> 00:31:08.800 align:middle line:84%
we are actually missing
the plot here because if we

00:31:08.800 --> 00:31:10.210 align:middle line:90%
don't actually deal--

00:31:10.210 --> 00:31:13.068 align:middle line:84%
and that unfortunately would
need substantive changes

00:31:13.068 --> 00:31:14.110 align:middle line:90%
to everybody's lifestyle.

00:31:14.110 --> 00:31:14.230 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, dramatic changes.

00:31:14.230 --> 00:31:16.210 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Like,
we'd have to reel back

00:31:16.210 --> 00:31:18.040 align:middle line:90%
in a lot of the excess.

00:31:18.040 --> 00:31:21.260 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you'd have to shoot
this on Skype or something

00:31:21.260 --> 00:31:22.510 align:middle line:90%
rather than flying every week.

00:31:22.510 --> 00:31:25.090 align:middle line:90%


00:31:25.090 --> 00:31:26.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm only doing this--

00:31:26.310 --> 00:31:28.313 align:middle line:84%
and I wish, as I
said, at this point,

00:31:28.313 --> 00:31:30.730 align:middle line:84%
I wish I'd just gone the Tony
Robbins route and been like,

00:31:30.730 --> 00:31:34.960 align:middle line:84%
yeah, we could all
have incredible lives.

00:31:34.960 --> 00:31:37.780 align:middle line:84%
Again, the other sad
thing is the excess

00:31:37.780 --> 00:31:40.420 align:middle line:84%
that the Western world
has used has really

00:31:40.420 --> 00:31:41.860 align:middle line:90%
cost the developing world.

00:31:41.860 --> 00:31:45.400 align:middle line:84%
Like Bangladesh, let's
say, 170 million people who

00:31:45.400 --> 00:31:48.670 align:middle line:90%
live very close to sea level.

00:31:48.670 --> 00:31:52.630 align:middle line:84%
They are the ones who are
most likely to be wiped out

00:31:52.630 --> 00:31:55.360 align:middle line:84%
as the seas start to rise
because they're not going

00:31:55.360 --> 00:31:56.590 align:middle line:90%
to be able to farm and so on.

00:31:56.590 --> 00:31:58.060 align:middle line:90%
That's really us who did that.

00:31:58.060 --> 00:32:00.340 align:middle line:84%
The US used something
like 25% or more

00:32:00.340 --> 00:32:02.800 align:middle line:84%
of the Earth's
resources and carbon.

00:32:02.800 --> 00:32:04.810 align:middle line:90%
Europe also used a lot.

00:32:04.810 --> 00:32:08.530 align:middle line:84%
Even though China and India
and so on are now catching up,

00:32:08.530 --> 00:32:11.410 align:middle line:84%
we're very much responsible
for a lot of what's

00:32:11.410 --> 00:32:13.540 align:middle line:84%
happened to the
planet, and we're still

00:32:13.540 --> 00:32:14.750 align:middle line:90%
not taking responsibility.

00:32:14.750 --> 00:32:16.840 align:middle line:84%
In fact, we've elected
somebody who represents

00:32:16.840 --> 00:32:18.640 align:middle line:90%
like total irresponsibility.

00:32:18.640 --> 00:32:21.892 align:middle line:84%
So we have to take this as
something very personal.

00:32:21.892 --> 00:32:23.350 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: There was
an area, I think

00:32:23.350 --> 00:32:25.392 align:middle line:10%
it might have been India,
where a quarter million

00:32:25.392 --> 00:32:29.140 align:middle line:10%
