because they weren't

00:32:29.140 --> 00:32:32.650 align:middle line:10%
happy with the way their crops
were coming because they were

00:32:32.650 --> 00:32:35.020 align:middle line:10%
genetically modified
and everything else.

00:32:35.020 --> 00:32:36.370 align:middle line:90%
That's horrible.

00:32:36.370 --> 00:32:39.220 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Well, yeah,
corporations have unfortunately

00:32:39.220 --> 00:32:42.940 align:middle line:84%
been willing to do a lot
of things for profit--

00:32:42.940 --> 00:32:46.870 align:middle line:84%
whether it's denying
generic AIDS drugs to Africa

00:32:46.870 --> 00:32:50.440 align:middle line:84%
or giving Indian
farmers seeds that

00:32:50.440 --> 00:32:52.390 align:middle line:84%
have to be rebought
every year and so on.

00:32:52.390 --> 00:32:53.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sure, or
cancer-causing herbicides.

00:32:53.610 --> 00:32:54.970 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: You know,
it just shows you

00:32:54.970 --> 00:32:56.620 align:middle line:84%
how ridiculous the
system is because we

00:32:56.620 --> 00:32:58.540 align:middle line:84%
have these incredible
technologies,

00:32:58.540 --> 00:33:00.050 align:middle line:84%
and we could be
sharing them, but we

00:33:00.050 --> 00:33:04.220 align:middle line:84%
can't do it under the current
economic political model.

00:33:04.220 --> 00:33:07.760 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: When you look at where
you've come over the last years

00:33:07.760 --> 00:33:09.710 align:middle line:10%
since your books
have been coming out,

00:33:09.710 --> 00:33:12.073 align:middle line:10%
have you changed too?

00:33:12.073 --> 00:33:13.490 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah,
I'm still going

00:33:13.490 --> 00:33:14.690 align:middle line:90%
through a lot of changing.

00:33:14.690 --> 00:33:15.140 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You are?

00:33:15.140 --> 00:33:15.940 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah.

00:33:15.940 --> 00:33:17.580 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: In what direction?

00:33:17.580 --> 00:33:21.110 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Well, one thing is,
in the wake of the whole MeToo

00:33:21.110 --> 00:33:24.800 align:middle line:84%
movement, addressing my own
areas of toxic masculinity

00:33:24.800 --> 00:33:29.480 align:middle line:84%
and facing that and
realizing that I

00:33:29.480 --> 00:33:31.730 align:middle line:84%
made a lot of mistakes
in how I dealt

00:33:31.730 --> 00:33:34.180 align:middle line:90%
with women and the feminine.

00:33:34.180 --> 00:33:37.280 align:middle line:84%
That's been a major
ongoing area that I've

00:33:37.280 --> 00:33:38.810 align:middle line:90%
been seeking to address.

00:33:38.810 --> 00:33:41.510 align:middle line:84%
And then also, in a way,
I'm in a more nebulous zone

00:33:41.510 --> 00:33:43.458 align:middle line:84%
of uncertainty
because I was trying

00:33:43.458 --> 00:33:45.500 align:middle line:84%
to start a whole company
and a movement, Evolver.

00:33:45.500 --> 00:33:48.110 align:middle line:90%


00:33:48.110 --> 00:33:49.880 align:middle line:84%
Then that, for
whatever reasons--

00:33:49.880 --> 00:33:52.213 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's still going, but
I'm not actively involved.

00:33:52.213 --> 00:33:54.870 align:middle line:84%
So I'm kind of open to
the mystery at this point.

00:33:54.870 --> 00:33:57.500 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: You had mentioned
earlier about crop formations.

00:33:57.500 --> 00:34:00.590 align:middle line:84%
And of course, they're
all over the planet.

00:34:00.590 --> 00:34:02.060 align:middle line:90%
What's your take on that?

00:34:02.060 --> 00:34:03.320 align:middle line:90%
Who's doing these things?

00:34:03.320 --> 00:34:05.570 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah, well,
I definitely think that--

00:34:05.570 --> 00:34:08.540 align:middle line:84%
I spent one solid
summer and then

00:34:08.540 --> 00:34:10.580 align:middle line:84%
part of another
summer in Glastonbury

00:34:10.580 --> 00:34:14.659 align:middle line:84%
going to them as they
popped up and researching,

00:34:14.659 --> 00:34:17.100 align:middle line:84%
talking to all the people
involved with them.

00:34:17.100 --> 00:34:21.689 align:middle line:84%
And I do think that there's
a non-human intelligence--

00:34:21.689 --> 00:34:22.489 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You do?

00:34:22.489 --> 00:34:24.239 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: --that
is involved with this.

00:34:24.239 --> 00:34:26.719 align:middle line:84%
There's some higher
form of intelligence

00:34:26.719 --> 00:34:29.600 align:middle line:84%
that is using this as a
medium for communication

00:34:29.600 --> 00:34:30.790 align:middle line:90%
and a very playful one.

00:34:30.790 --> 00:34:33.031 align:middle line:90%
And it seems to be in a way--

00:34:33.031 --> 00:34:34.489 align:middle line:84%
what I took from
it, after spending

00:34:34.489 --> 00:34:35.989 align:middle line:84%
so much time looking
at it, was it's

00:34:35.989 --> 00:34:39.530 align:middle line:84%
like a kind of a teaching
on the nature of reality

00:34:39.530 --> 00:34:41.870 align:middle line:84%
and the nature of
consciousness and giving us

00:34:41.870 --> 00:34:45.350 align:middle line:84%
these very gentle hints
about the importance

00:34:45.350 --> 00:34:48.710 align:middle line:84%
of sacred geometries,
the importance of symbols

00:34:48.710 --> 00:34:50.449 align:middle line:90%
from ancient cultures and so on.

00:34:50.449 --> 00:34:52.885 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But you do think
it's an ET presence?

00:34:52.885 --> 00:34:54.218 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Well, I don't know.

00:34:54.218 --> 00:34:56.719 align:middle line:84%
I think ET is a
complicated word.

00:34:56.719 --> 00:34:58.610 align:middle line:84%
I think that there
may be other levels

00:34:58.610 --> 00:35:00.920 align:middle line:84%
of galactic intelligence,
and there also

00:35:00.920 --> 00:35:02.730 align:middle line:90%
may be other dimensions.

00:35:02.730 --> 00:35:06.260 align:middle line:84%
We know that, according
to contemporary physics,

00:35:06.260 --> 00:35:09.530 align:middle line:84%
they talk about there being
10 dimensions of space time.

00:35:09.530 --> 00:35:12.770 align:middle line:84%
What we're experiencing now
is the fourth dimension.

00:35:12.770 --> 00:35:14.690 align:middle line:84%
If there were forms
of consciousness

00:35:14.690 --> 00:35:16.580 align:middle line:84%
that were in the sixth
or seventh dimension,

00:35:16.580 --> 00:35:19.280 align:middle line:84%
they would be able to
potentially move through time

00:35:19.280 --> 00:35:21.580 align:middle line:90%
as we move through space.

00:35:21.580 --> 00:35:24.255 align:middle line:84%
They might be us in
another dimension

00:35:24.255 --> 00:35:25.380 align:middle line:90%
in what we call the future.

00:35:25.380 --> 00:35:28.900 align:middle line:84%
But they would just be
existing in their relationship

00:35:28.900 --> 00:35:32.070 align:middle line:90%
to their dimensional reality.

00:35:32.070 --> 00:35:36.290 align:middle line:84%
We've tended to make a very
literalistic and reductive

00:35:36.290 --> 00:35:38.900 align:middle line:84%
discussion around subjects
like ETs and so on,

00:35:38.900 --> 00:35:40.887 align:middle line:90%
and it may be much more complex.

00:35:40.887 --> 00:35:42.720 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: What about the
possibility, Daniel,

00:35:42.720 --> 00:35:45.320 align:middle line:10%
that this planet--
again, the Gaia Theory--

00:35:45.320 --> 00:35:49.790 align:middle line:10%
is alive, and it's the
planet sending us messages.

00:35:49.790 --> 00:35:51.838 align:middle line:10%
That's how it
communicates with us--

00:35:51.838 --> 00:35:52.880 align:middle line:10%
through these formations.

00:35:52.880 --> 00:35:53.120 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Right.

00:35:53.120 --> 00:35:54.690 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't really
make sense to me.

00:35:54.690 --> 00:35:56.315 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think the
planet communicates

00:35:56.315 --> 00:35:59.870 align:middle line:84%
to us through flowers and
bumblebees and streams

00:35:59.870 --> 00:36:01.430 align:middle line:90%
and clouds and so on.

00:36:01.430 --> 00:36:04.725 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And mosquitoes.

00:36:04.725 --> 00:36:08.435 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: And mosquitoes
and ticks and moles and snakes.

00:36:08.435 --> 00:36:10.310 align:middle line:84%
I don't think the planet
needs to communicate

00:36:10.310 --> 00:36:12.460 align:middle line:84%
with us through these types
of geometric patterns.

00:36:12.460 --> 00:36:14.180 align:middle line:84%
These suggest more
of an ordered,

00:36:14.180 --> 00:36:17.330 align:middle line:84%
kind of civilizational
imposition in a way.

00:36:17.330 --> 00:36:20.930 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: In your new book, of
course, "When Plants Dream,"

00:36:20.930 --> 00:36:23.510 align:middle line:10%
you talk about the global
spread of ayahuasca.

00:36:23.510 --> 00:36:25.680 align:middle line:84%
Tell us what it
is, first of all.

00:36:25.680 --> 00:36:28.250 align:middle line:84%
What is ayahuasca,
and what does it do?

00:36:28.250 --> 00:36:32.630 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah, so ayahuasca
is a visionary potion from

00:36:32.630 --> 00:36:36.140 align:middle line:84%
the Amazon basin, a tea in a
sense that's usually brewed

00:36:36.140 --> 00:36:37.820 align:middle line:84%
together from two
different plants--

00:36:37.820 --> 00:36:41.090 align:middle line:84%
the ayahuasca vine,
Banisteriopsis caapi,

00:36:41.090 --> 00:36:44.450 align:middle line:84%
which contains certain compounds
that are like harmaline,

00:36:44.450 --> 00:36:46.030 align:middle line:90%
which are MAO inhibitors.

00:36:46.030 --> 00:36:51.260 align:middle line:84%
And then you have the leaves
of the chacruna, which

00:36:51.260 --> 00:36:55.718 align:middle line:84%
contain Psychotria
viridis, which contain

00:36:55.718 --> 00:36:57.010 align:middle line:90%
Dimethyltryptamine, or GMT DMT.

00:36:57.010 --> 00:36:59.780 align:middle line:90%


00:36:59.780 --> 00:37:04.590 align:middle line:84%
DMT, if you try to eat it, it's
normally inactivated by enzymes

00:37:04.590 --> 00:37:07.070 align:middle line:84%
But if you put it
together in this potion,

00:37:07.070 --> 00:37:08.180 align:middle line:90%
then it can be taken in.

00:37:08.180 --> 00:37:09.222 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Do you drink it?

00:37:09.222 --> 00:37:10.898 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: You drink it.

00:37:10.898 --> 00:37:12.440 align:middle line:84%
Usually the ceremonies
are all night.

00:37:12.440 --> 00:37:14.790 align:middle line:84%
Usually you have a
shaman or a group of them

00:37:14.790 --> 00:37:16.370 align:middle line:90%
who preside over it.

00:37:16.370 --> 00:37:17.360 align:middle line:90%
Often they're singing.

00:37:17.360 --> 00:37:20.210 align:middle line:90%
Often there's healing rituals--

00:37:20.210 --> 00:37:22.750 align:middle line:90%
prayers, tobacco, chanting.

00:37:22.750 --> 00:37:24.980 align:middle line:84%
And you know, many
people find this

00:37:24.980 --> 00:37:28.843 align:middle line:84%
to be a very, very powerful
and profound experience--

00:37:28.843 --> 00:37:30.260 align:middle line:84%
in some cases, a
very healing one.

00:37:30.260 --> 00:37:32.797 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Does it knock you out?

00:37:32.797 --> 00:37:34.130 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: It knocks you down.

00:37:34.130 --> 00:37:38.450 align:middle line:84%
Definitely you're in a different
state of consciousness.

00:37:38.450 --> 00:37:39.480 align:middle line:90%
You're conscious.

00:37:39.480 --> 00:37:39.950 align:middle line:90%
You're awake.

00:37:39.950 --> 00:37:41.640 align:middle line:84%
But it's almost like
you're in like a--

00:37:41.640 --> 00:37:42.290 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: A different zone?

00:37:42.290 --> 00:37:44.240 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: --visionary
dream cocoon,

00:37:44.240 --> 00:37:46.850 align:middle line:84%
where you're seeing into
these other realities.

00:37:46.850 --> 00:37:49.610 align:middle line:84%
And sound has an
incredible effect on you,

00:37:49.610 --> 00:37:50.750 align:middle line:90%
or smell, or whatever.

00:37:50.750 --> 00:37:51.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Everything's enhanced?

00:37:51.800 --> 00:37:53.550 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Everything
is enhanced, yeah.

00:37:53.550 --> 00:37:56.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would you get in a
car and drive after doing this?

00:37:56.120 --> 00:37:57.470 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: After doing
it, you could, sure.

00:37:57.470 --> 00:37:58.940 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the next
day most people

00:37:58.940 --> 00:38:01.310 align:middle line:84%
feel really very
much in their bodies.

00:38:01.310 --> 00:38:05.000 align:middle line:84%
And also the MAO inhibitors
that the ayahuasca vine

00:38:05.000 --> 00:38:08.630 align:middle line:84%
contains have a natural
antidepressant effect.

00:38:08.630 --> 00:38:11.055 align:middle line:84%
So they really lift your
spirits, often generally.

00:38:11.055 --> 00:38:12.825 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're a little more
energetic and everything else.

00:38:12.825 --> 00:38:13.625 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah.

00:38:13.625 --> 00:38:15.650 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not saying that
it's for everybody.

00:38:15.650 --> 00:38:19.100 align:middle line:84%
Everybody has an individual
decision around it you.

00:38:19.100 --> 00:38:20.925 align:middle line:84%
It is a very
profound experience.

00:38:20.925 --> 00:38:21.725 align:middle line:90%
It can be jarring.

00:38:21.725 --> 00:38:24.230 align:middle line:90%


00:38:24.230 --> 00:38:27.890 align:middle line:90%
So it's an individual decision.

00:38:27.890 --> 00:38:29.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We have
a program on Gaia

00:38:29.360 --> 00:38:34.343 align:middle line:84%
called "Psychedelica" which
addresses this exact topic.

00:38:34.343 --> 00:38:36.800 align:middle line:10%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:38:36.800 --> 00:38:39.290 align:middle line:10%
>> Deep in the
heart of the Amazon,

00:38:39.290 --> 00:38:44.240 align:middle line:10%
out of generations of indigenous
people from mysterious origins,

00:38:44.240 --> 00:38:47.690 align:middle line:10%
birth from a specific
combination of plants comes

00:38:47.690 --> 00:38:52.340 align:middle line:10%
a visionary experience, an
ancient healing tradition--

00:38:52.340 --> 00:38:54.710 align:middle line:10%
modern controversy
and massive interest

00:38:54.710 --> 00:38:58.850 align:middle line:10%
from younger generations all
surrounding a sacred brew

00:38:58.850 --> 00:39:03.790 align:middle line:10%
called ayahuasca, a
beverage that contains DMT.

00:39:03.790 --> 00:39:07.550 align:middle line:10%
DMT is a tryptamine that
