00:39:07.550 --> 00:39:10.520 align:middle line:10%
But the chacruna leaves
contains much more.

00:39:10.520 --> 00:39:13.550 align:middle line:10%
Left alone, this molecule
will be metabolized

00:39:13.550 --> 00:39:15.600 align:middle line:10%
before having any effect.

00:39:15.600 --> 00:39:18.740 align:middle line:10%
So the sacred vine is
added to protect its entry

00:39:18.740 --> 00:39:23.270 align:middle line:10%
through the body into the
brain and into our experience.

00:39:23.270 --> 00:39:28.050 align:middle line:90%


00:39:28.050 --> 00:39:31.020 align:middle line:10%
From scientists to
shamans, many theories

00:39:31.020 --> 00:39:34.380 align:middle line:10%
abound regarding the strange
effects of ayahuasca.

00:39:34.380 --> 00:39:37.800 align:middle line:10%
And yet it still is
not fully understood.

00:39:37.800 --> 00:39:40.320 align:middle line:10%
>>DENNIS MCKENNA:
So ayahuasca is--

00:39:40.320 --> 00:39:44.910 align:middle line:10%
it's a whole bunch of things,
but on the nuts and bolts

00:39:44.910 --> 00:39:46.380 align:middle line:10%
level, it's a beverage.

00:39:46.380 --> 00:39:50.100 align:middle line:10%
It's made from two plants
at least, one of which

00:39:50.100 --> 00:39:53.310 align:middle line:10%
contains Dimethyltryptamine.

00:39:53.310 --> 00:39:56.460 align:middle line:10%
At the cultural level, it's
much broader than that.

00:39:56.460 --> 00:39:58.680 align:middle line:84%
These are essentially
shamanic practices,

00:39:58.680 --> 00:40:02.820 align:middle line:84%
and ayahuasca is at
the center of that kind

00:40:02.820 --> 00:40:07.410 align:middle line:84%
of traditional medicine,
which is really

00:40:07.410 --> 00:40:10.170 align:middle line:90%
a mind-body kind of medicine.

00:40:10.170 --> 00:40:13.800 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Daniel, is ayahuasca
legal in this country, or is

00:40:13.800 --> 00:40:15.250 align:middle line:90%
it considered a narcotic?

00:40:15.250 --> 00:40:16.290 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:40:16.290 --> 00:40:17.260 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: The
legality is something

00:40:17.260 --> 00:40:18.210 align:middle line:90%
that we track in the book.

00:40:18.210 --> 00:40:19.543 align:middle line:90%
And it's actually quite complex.

00:40:19.543 --> 00:40:22.163 align:middle line:90%


00:40:22.163 --> 00:40:23.580 align:middle line:84%
There's a couple
of religions that

00:40:23.580 --> 00:40:25.300 align:middle line:84%
started in Brazil
in the 1920s that

00:40:25.300 --> 00:40:27.690 align:middle line:84%
are syncretic religions,
that mix together

00:40:27.690 --> 00:40:30.010 align:middle line:84%
Christian and
indigenous elements.

00:40:30.010 --> 00:40:32.130 align:middle line:84%
One of them is called
Uniao do Vegetales,

00:40:32.130 --> 00:40:37.110 align:middle line:84%
and they actually won a Supreme
Court case a number of years

00:40:37.110 --> 00:40:42.720 align:middle line:84%
ago allowing them to use their
ayahuasca tea as a sacrament.

00:40:42.720 --> 00:40:46.980 align:middle line:84%
Based on that decision,
a court in Oregon

00:40:46.980 --> 00:40:48.750 align:middle line:84%
allowed another
religion, Santo Daime,

00:40:48.750 --> 00:40:51.900 align:middle line:84%
to have protection for
their use of the sacrament.

00:40:51.900 --> 00:40:57.210 align:middle line:84%
And at the moment, there
seems to be a general sense

00:40:57.210 --> 00:40:59.200 align:middle line:90%
that it's OK.

00:40:59.200 --> 00:41:02.140 align:middle line:84%
People have been
advertising publicly.

00:41:02.140 --> 00:41:05.400 align:middle line:10%
This guy in Florida has been
very public about putting

00:41:05.400 --> 00:41:07.200 align:middle line:10%
Facebook ads on about it.

00:41:07.200 --> 00:41:09.630 align:middle line:84%
And it seems like
as long as there's

00:41:09.630 --> 00:41:15.180 align:middle line:84%
some type of religious
connection, sacramental use

00:41:15.180 --> 00:41:18.015 align:middle line:84%
of it, it seems like it's
being allowed at this point.

00:41:18.015 --> 00:41:19.140 align:middle line:90%
But it's still a gray area.

00:41:19.140 --> 00:41:21.510 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: If you were driving
and got stopped by police,

00:41:21.510 --> 00:41:24.977 align:middle line:10%
and you had a little container
of it, what would they do?

00:41:24.977 --> 00:41:26.810 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: They
wouldn't know what it was.

00:41:26.810 --> 00:41:28.170 align:middle line:90%
It's a very minor--

00:41:28.170 --> 00:41:30.810 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's not
meth or anything.

00:41:30.810 --> 00:41:33.090 align:middle line:84%
A very small group of
people are doing it,

00:41:33.090 --> 00:41:35.060 align:middle line:84%
and they're doing
it in ceremony.

00:41:35.060 --> 00:41:36.850 align:middle line:84%
You're not going
to do it and drive.

00:41:36.850 --> 00:41:38.100 align:middle line:90%
It's just not going to happen.

00:41:38.100 --> 00:41:39.990 align:middle line:90%
It would be a very stupid idea.

00:41:39.990 --> 00:41:42.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But it seems to
enhance your abilities

00:41:42.390 --> 00:41:43.560 align:middle line:90%
for all kinds of things.

00:41:43.560 --> 00:41:45.360 align:middle line:90%
Does it make you more intuitive?

00:41:45.360 --> 00:41:46.160 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Yes.

00:41:46.160 --> 00:41:48.370 align:middle line:84%
I think it can help you
enhance your intuition.

00:41:48.370 --> 00:41:50.787 align:middle line:84%
What I've been very fascinated,
which we track in the book

00:41:50.787 --> 00:41:56.220 align:middle line:84%
also, is how some people who
are very successful or come

00:41:56.220 --> 00:41:59.820 align:middle line:84%
from wealthy backgrounds,
the ayahuasca

00:41:59.820 --> 00:42:05.130 align:middle line:84%
really changes their thinking
about how they use their power

00:42:05.130 --> 00:42:06.917 align:middle line:90%
in relationship to the planet.

00:42:06.917 --> 00:42:08.500 align:middle line:84%
So for instance, we
talked about there

00:42:08.500 --> 00:42:12.450 align:middle line:84%
was a CEO who was running
a soft drink company.

00:42:12.450 --> 00:42:14.508 align:middle line:84%
He drank ayahuasca,
and then he realized

00:42:14.508 --> 00:42:16.050 align:middle line:84%
that he didn't wanted
to do something

00:42:16.050 --> 00:42:18.697 align:middle line:84%
that was just sugar drinks
that were for mass consumption.

00:42:18.697 --> 00:42:19.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He changed?

00:42:19.530 --> 00:42:21.540 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: So
he shifted to more

00:42:21.540 --> 00:42:24.561 align:middle line:84%
of a health-based product that
had more herbal benefits and so

00:42:24.561 --> 00:42:24.650 align:middle line:90%
on.

00:42:24.650 --> 00:42:26.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He probably
ended up making more money

00:42:26.250 --> 00:42:27.370 align:middle line:90%
in the long run.

00:42:27.370 --> 00:42:31.080 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Well that's
also arguably possible.

00:42:31.080 --> 00:42:33.950 align:middle line:90%
But it does seem to really--

00:42:33.950 --> 00:42:36.960 align:middle line:84%
it's a powerful tool both
for inner exploration,

00:42:36.960 --> 00:42:40.140 align:middle line:84%
for discovering that there
maybe are these other layers

00:42:40.140 --> 00:42:42.283 align:middle line:84%
or dimensions of
spiritual reality.

00:42:42.283 --> 00:42:43.950 align:middle line:84%
And then also for
some people, it really

00:42:43.950 --> 00:42:49.500 align:middle line:84%
helps them to address, yeah,
how they use their resources--

00:42:49.500 --> 00:42:52.168 align:middle line:84%
recalibrate based on
having a deeper connection

00:42:52.168 --> 00:42:54.210 align:middle line:84%
to the Gaian intelligence
of the planet, perhaps.

00:42:54.210 --> 00:42:55.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:42:55.020 --> 00:42:57.210 align:middle line:84%
Your first book was called,
"Breaking Open the Head?"

00:42:57.210 --> 00:42:57.960 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: "Breaking
Open the Head."

00:42:57.960 --> 00:42:59.460 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Which dealt with this.

00:42:59.460 --> 00:43:01.335 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah, that
book was an overview.

00:43:01.335 --> 00:43:05.870 align:middle line:84%
So that really was about
my own journeys, discovery

00:43:05.870 --> 00:43:07.067 align:middle line:90%
starting in my late 20s.

00:43:07.067 --> 00:43:08.650 align:middle line:84%
I was a journalist,
and I went through

00:43:08.650 --> 00:43:11.443 align:middle line:90%
a spiritual existential crisis.

00:43:11.443 --> 00:43:13.860 align:middle line:84%
I remembered that I had taken
LSD and mushrooms in college

00:43:13.860 --> 00:43:15.700 align:middle line:90%
and decided to explore that.

00:43:15.700 --> 00:43:17.700 align:middle line:84%
But this was back in
the 1990s in New York,

00:43:17.700 --> 00:43:20.520 align:middle line:84%
and you couldn't even talk
about psychedelics in public

00:43:20.520 --> 00:43:21.870 align:middle line:90%
without people laughing at you.

00:43:21.870 --> 00:43:23.415 align:middle line:84%
Or if I brought it
up to my friends

00:43:23.415 --> 00:43:25.290 align:middle line:84%
who were journalists or
editors or whatever--

00:43:25.290 --> 00:43:26.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It was
too "foo-foo" then.

00:43:26.730 --> 00:43:27.530 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Yes.

00:43:27.530 --> 00:43:29.430 align:middle line:84%
There had been a
huge cultural effort

00:43:29.430 --> 00:43:34.780 align:middle line:84%
to ridicule psychedelics,
to make them seem absurd.

00:43:34.780 --> 00:43:38.190 align:middle line:84%
Once they were outlawed
in the '60s and '70s, you

00:43:38.190 --> 00:43:39.180 align:middle line:90%
couldn't even--

00:43:39.180 --> 00:43:42.010 align:middle line:84%
basically science had
made them totally taboo.

00:43:42.010 --> 00:43:46.080 align:middle line:84%
So basically from the early
'70s to the late '90s,

00:43:46.080 --> 00:43:50.130 align:middle line:84%
there were basically no
tests using human subjects

00:43:50.130 --> 00:43:52.758 align:middle line:84%
with psychedelics,
even though in the '50s

00:43:52.758 --> 00:43:54.300 align:middle line:84%
psychologists were
talking about them

00:43:54.300 --> 00:43:56.340 align:middle line:84%
as the most incredible
tools we had ever

00:43:56.340 --> 00:43:59.520 align:middle line:84%
found for studying the
human mind and so on.

00:43:59.520 --> 00:44:01.030 align:middle line:84%
So it's only in
the last 15 years,

00:44:01.030 --> 00:44:02.550 align:middle line:84%
actually since "Breaking
Open the Head" came out,

00:44:02.550 --> 00:44:04.140 align:middle line:84%
and I think that
that book may have

00:44:04.140 --> 00:44:07.440 align:middle line:84%
helped to shift the
cultural tonality maybe

00:44:07.440 --> 00:44:09.470 align:middle line:90%
around the psychedelics.

00:44:09.470 --> 00:44:11.910 align:middle line:84%
Now we're seeing this massive
psychedelic Renaissance,

00:44:11.910 --> 00:44:15.533 align:middle line:84%
and the discoveries
are really amazing.

00:44:15.533 --> 00:44:16.950 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: I think
mushrooms are now

00:44:16.950 --> 00:44:19.007 align:middle line:10%
legal in this state,
Colorado, aren't they?

00:44:19.007 --> 00:44:21.340 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: I think it's--
is it just in Denver, maybe?

00:44:21.340 --> 00:44:22.140 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Maybe.

00:44:22.140 --> 00:44:24.535 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah, that just
happened a few weeks ago.

00:44:24.535 --> 00:44:25.410 align:middle line:90%
That's extraordinary.

00:44:25.410 --> 00:44:28.270 align:middle line:84%
And they've done
some great studies.

00:44:28.270 --> 00:44:32.270 align:middle line:84%
Johns Hopkins did a study where
they gave mushrooms to people

00:44:32.270 --> 00:44:34.270 align:middle line:84%
who'd never had a psychedelic
experience before,

00:44:34.270 --> 00:44:36.910 align:middle line:84%
then over a series of years
charted them-- you know,

00:44:36.910 --> 00:44:39.940 align:middle line:84%
went back to them and did
psychological testing--

00:44:39.940 --> 00:44:41.530 align:middle line:84%
and found that people
remembered them

00:44:41.530 --> 00:44:43.930 align:middle line:84%
as one of the greatest
experiences of their lives,

00:44:43.930 --> 00:44:46.300 align:middle line:84%
in parallel with the
birth of their first child

00:44:46.300 --> 00:44:51.220 align:middle line:84%
or their wedding, and had
permanent positive changes

00:44:51.220 --> 00:44:52.480 align:middle line:90%
to their psychological makeup.

00:44:52.480 --> 00:44:54.760 align:middle line:84%
So for instance, they
permanently had more openness

00:44:54.760 --> 00:44:58.240 align:middle line:90%
to new experience as a factor.

00:44:58.240 --> 00:45:00.310 align:middle line:90%
So that's very exciting.

00:45:00.310 --> 00:45:03.180 align:middle line:84%
We're seeing treatments for
obsessive compulsive disorder,

00:45:03.180 --> 00:45:04.200 align:middle line:90%
for depression.

00:45:04.200 --> 00:45:05.890 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Autism?

00:45:05.890 --> 00:45:08.920 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Autism is an
interesting possibility.

00:45:08.920 --> 00:45:11.980 align:middle line:84%
In the book on
ayahuasca, we found

00:45:11.980 --> 00:45:15.370 align:middle line:84%
a researcher who's
demonstrated that ayahuasca

00:45:15.370 --> 00:45:19.938 align:middle line:84%
can help actually grow new
brain cells, neurogenesis.

00:45:19.938 --> 00:45:20.980 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: That's dramatic.

00:45:20.980 --> 00:45:21.790 align:middle line:10%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah.

00:45:21.790 --> 00:45:23.920 align:middle line:84%
So that might have really
interesting implications

00:45:23.920 --> 00:45:26.530 align:middle line:84%
down the line when we
can isolate some of that.

00:45:26.530 --> 00:45:30.100 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: PTSD-- huge problem
with our military, huge problem

00:45:30.100 --> 00:45:31.640 align:middle line:10%
with individuals as well.

00:45:31.640 --> 00:45:32.440 align:middle line:90%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah.

00:45:32.440 --> 00:45:38.980 align:middle line:84%
So MAPS has been running
clinical trials with MDMA

00:45:38.980 --> 00:45:40.690 align:middle line:84%
for treating
post-traumatic stress

00:45:40.690 --> 00:45:43.730 align:middle line:84%
disorder in veterans from the
Iraq and Afghanistan wars.

00:45:43.730 --> 00:45:47.170 align:middle line:84%
And I think they've had
something like a 60% success

00:45:47.170 --> 00:45:51.280 align:middle line:84%
rate where you give MDMA in
therapy-assisted sessions

00:45:51.280 --> 00:45:52.810 align:middle line:90%
three times.

00:45:52.810 --> 00:45:54.880 align:middle line:84%
And you don't even
really do that much.

00:45:54.880 --> 00:45:58.000 align:middle line:84%
You just wait for the
repressed emotions

00:45:58.000 --> 00:46:03.330 align:middle line:84%
and experiences to surface
and hold container for them.

00:46:03.330 --> 00:46:05.860 align:middle line:84%
And ayahuasca, actually
there's a wonderful film

00:46:05.860 --> 00:46:07.510 align:middle line:84%
that just came out
called "From Shock

00:46:07.510 --> 00:46:11.870 align:middle line:84%
to Awe" which traces
some Iraq war veterans.

00:46:11.870 --> 00:46:14.950 align:middle line:84%
And they show these
huge medicine cabinets

00:46:14.950 --> 00:46:16.990 align:middle line:84%
full of all these
pharmaceuticals and so on.

00:46:16.990 --> 00:46:17.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Horrible, yeah.

00:46:17.530 --> 00:46:19.370 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: And then they drink
ayahuasca for a few months,

00:46:19.370 --> 00:46:20.620 align:middle line:84%
so they just throw
away all those pills.

00:46:20.620 --> 00:46:22.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Throw the
other stuff out--

00:46:22.120 --> 00:46:23.540 align:middle line:90%
that's dramatic.

00:46:23.540 --> 00:46:26.230 align:middle line:84%
Can it hurt you
at all, ayahuasca?

00:46:26.230 --> 00:46:30.270 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: So like any
powerful psychoactive

00:46:30.270 --> 00:46:35.635 align:middle line:84%
or psychedelic, it
has the potential to--

00:46:35.635 --> 00:46:38.740 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if it can
cause psychological harm

00:46:38.740 --> 00:46:41.230 align:middle line:84%
or if it really just
opens up maybe stuff

00:46:41.230 --> 00:46:42.700 align:middle line:90%
that you'd repressed or so on.

00:46:42.700 --> 00:46:46.450 align:middle line:84%
But I do know people who've had
psychological breakdowns after.

00:46:46.450 --> 00:46:48.880 align:middle line:84%
But it's very rare, but it
does happen where people end up

00:46:48.880 --> 00:46:49.795 align:middle line:90%
in a mental institution.

00:46:49.795 --> 00:46:50.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Maybe
they had too much?

00:46:50.140 --> 00:46:51.848 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: Or they
maybe drank too much

00:46:51.848 --> 00:46:53.570 align:middle line:84%
in a short period
of time or whatever.

00:46:53.570 --> 00:46:55.930 align:middle line:84%
We're really just
learning about it.

00:46:55.930 --> 00:46:59.260 align:middle line:84%
But we also do have to remember
that even in the Amazon,

00:46:59.260 --> 00:47:01.480 align:middle line:84%
it's not like everybody
would take ayahuasca.

00:47:01.480 --> 00:47:03.730 align:middle line:84%
Often, it was really only
the shamans who would do it,

00:47:03.730 --> 00:47:05.660 align:middle line:84%
and they would diagnose
their patients.

00:47:05.660 --> 00:47:08.020 align:middle line:84%
But then also when you
took these types of things,

00:47:08.020 --> 00:47:10.720 align:middle line:90%
they were initiations.

00:47:10.720 --> 00:47:12.940 align:middle line:84%
Initiations are
meant to be scary.

00:47:12.940 --> 00:47:16.140 align:middle line:84%
It's like you're going into this
liminal world between the life

00:47:16.140 --> 00:47:16.940 align:middle line:90%
and death--

00:47:16.940 --> 00:47:18.790 align:middle line:84%
into the spirit world
to get knowledge,

00:47:18.790 --> 00:47:22.150 align:middle line:90%
to mature, to understand.

00:47:22.150 --> 00:47:23.740 align:middle line:84%
And those are
dangerous journeys,

00:47:23.740 --> 00:47:27.820 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes they can
cause negative consequences.

00:47:27.820 --> 00:47:29.650 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Daniel, if
you had a magic wand,

00:47:29.650 --> 00:47:32.380 align:middle line:10%
and you could just wave it over
the planet, what would that

00:47:32.380 --> 00:47:34.280 align:middle line:10%
wish be with that wand?

00:47:34.280 --> 00:47:36.970 align:middle line:10%
What would you
like to see happen?

00:47:36.970 --> 00:47:39.465 align:middle line:10%
>>PINCHBECK: Yeah,
I think we need--

00:47:39.465 --> 00:47:41.590 align:middle line:10%
I've mentioned Extinction
Rebellion and the Sunrise

00:47:41.590 --> 00:47:42.670 align:middle line:10%
Movement before--

00:47:42.670 --> 00:47:47.650 align:middle line:10%
we basically need a mass
global citizen movement,

00:47:47.650 --> 00:47:50.750 align:middle line:10%
you could say an uprising
or rebellion to some sense--

00:47:50.750 --> 00:47:53.080 align:middle line:10%
not a violent one, not
a destructive one--

00:47:53.080 --> 00:47:56.230 align:middle line:10%
but to recognize that
the system is broken,

00:47:56.230 --> 00:47:57.730 align:middle line:10%
and if we continue
along this path,

00:47:57.730 --> 00:47:59.647 align:middle line:10%
we're going to bring
about our own extinction.

00:47:59.647 --> 00:48:03.220 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, we have a very
small window of opportunity

00:48:03.220 --> 00:48:07.540 align:middle line:84%
to redesign our operating
system so that we

00:48:07.540 --> 00:48:12.430 align:middle line:84%
shift from exploitation and
extraction and domination

00:48:12.430 --> 00:48:15.875 align:middle line:84%
to really working to create
a regenerative system

00:48:15.875 --> 00:48:16.750 align:middle line:90%
on a planetary scale.

00:48:16.750 --> 00:48:18.310 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: How much
time do we have?

00:48:18.310 --> 00:48:21.210 align:middle line:84%
>>PINCHBECK: I think we better
get to it the next five years.

00:48:21.210 --> 00:48:22.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That soon?

